name: Timberline Lodge
summary: A fire broke out at the historic Timberline Lodge on Mount Hood in Oregon, prompting an evacuation. The lodge suffered minor damage but is expected to reopen on Saturday. The fire, which started in the attic, was quickly extinguished by firefighters. The cause of the fire is under investigation. The ski resort is closed until further notice. The lodge has been featured in movies, including "The Shining."
